    "It gave an average f1-score of 84.46% when trying to tell the difference between the four classes [141].Multi-branch fusion auxiliary learning (MBFAL) is a suggested approach for analyzing CXR images to diagnose pneumonia.",
    "The proposed MBFAL approach is comprised of ResNet34 and ResNet18, which were previously trained on the ImageNet dataset.",
    "The training was conducted using the ResNet18 and ResNet34 networks, the auxiliary learning method, the prior-attention residual learning (PARL) network, and the MBFAL technique.",
    "This technique is based on supplementary learning and verifying fit sets using an auxiliary database.",
    "This is performed in combination with the PARL structure and feature fusion approach."
